<br>
Esmalyn:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> That is just it. The list is not a guarantee that no one will &quot;KS.&quot; Those who believe everyone will abide by it are deluding themselves.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I could point to the four months without any drama over the camp except for the continual posts by guilds just finding out about this. I could point out that a standard camp is also not supported by Verant, and that by extension of your logic camp calls are pointless since not everyone will abide by them. But I'm sure you already knew these things.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Pala made his threat post on, what I think, was the assumption that disagreeing with the list implied a covert desire to go ganking Ragefires although no one made such a statement.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Honestly, though - do you think a guild that wants an epic but doesn't agree with the list won't attempt a ganking eventually? What other choice would they have, except perhaps to give up entirely? That's why the pro-list side fights so vehemently to convert people here - better to fight on the message board than to fight in Skyfire.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Barring nuclear holocaust there will always be a line at the post office. At the grocery store. There will always be bumper to bumper traffic. And there will always be a daily edition. The list is ridiculously long. I won't have to wait six months to buy stamps, groceries, reach the city, or buy the paper.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The list, whether in this order or in order of the power of people the clerics who want Ragefire can bring along, will always be there. Always. See that list? All those clerics want their epic, and they aren't going anywhere. If someone new wants to claim they're better than those people and should be ahead of them, that's at least honest. But make no mistake - that's what someone that wants to do away with the list is saying to the people on it: I'm better than you, I should go first.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Good God. How did burners come into this?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
How do you suppose people racing to kill Ragefire will kill him, with root-DoT? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The standard, especially in these low-customer service level days, will become clear: bring burners, or expect to lose the damage race.<br>
<br>
Ketel:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The content Verent has intraduced is not meant for everyone. If you play 10-20 or even 30 hours a week you should not EXPECT to get everything you want. People that put 50+ hours into this game DESERVE the rewards for ruining thier lives and eyesite<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Corrected a capitalization because I'm anal about such things. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Folks - that is what you get if there's no list. People who feel entitlement based on hours /played, and a trampling of the chances of smaller guilds to progress until everyone remotely associated with a fast-mobilizing guild moves on. Is that what you want, Yinta? Jlail? Instead of a list dominated by whatever guilds you feel dominate it now, would it be better if there was no written list but the next few months worth of spawns were dominated by LC, Wraith/Reviv, VM, Explicit/RIP, and the Alliance? Believe it or not, this might be your best chance at a cleric epic. It's certainly the option that has the least amount of hassle.<br>
<br>
Speaking of Jlail, how's it going? Be sure to /hug Stormgarh next time the two of you are on from me! Your points:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I have read the post and have seen little or no discussion concerning the points that Yinta made, that being that the list as it currently stands is not working.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Her analysis is based around an assessment of waiting time for someone joining now. As I pointed out above, some of the clerics on that list WILL end up waiting nine months to get their epic if all of them do - all you can do is juggle the order. Like At Death's Door and Wraith before you, you want to juggle the order to get ahead of others. And like ADD and Wraith before, hopefully you'll come to support this and join the list so that in a month's time some other guild can accuse you of stacking the list and being political. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I fail to see how only clerics can engage in logical discussion of this issue &lt;shrug&gt;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
In all solutions I've seen presented here, it's the cleric that has to sit out in Skyfire to get an item that their guild is very keen on them getting. If you want to talk about &quot;fair&quot;, wouldn't it only be fair to let those that make the biggest sacrifice decide how they'll do it? They seem to have come up with a system that's had four gank-free months - why not give them the benefit of the doubt?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I find it very amusing that many of the guilds that have KSed either myself or others in my presence, or who have stated that it is their position that the sever is FFA, can even consider now supporting the list.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
These guilds came to the conclusion, I imagine, that all the effort that they'd have to put into this camp were it FFA would be much better spent in other areas. When Ragefire is FFA, you have to devote a lot of man-hours to get a SHOT at it when it pops. You also have to deal with the inevitable grief that comes when two pullers &quot;don't see&quot; one another, or an &quot;engaged&quot; mob is fired upon. It's not worth it. It's especially not worth the grief it causes the cleric. How would you feel about a new piece of loot if you knew you had to beat someone else that had also sat there for days to get it?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I have seen no evidence (although I am sure it is in another thread somewhere) to repudiate any of the following: that non main characters are on the list, that certain guilds seem to be overly represented on the list, that getting on the list is a political exercise, that no consideration is given for having completed other steps of the epic, that the list creation was controlled by a few individuals on the server, that the list is controlled by a few individuals on the server, that stacking of friends and guildmates on the list has been perpetrated by those that control it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Whether non-mains are on the list or not, or should be or not, is a matter for the clerics involved to decide. My guildleader's cleric, Bennea, got her epic by being on the list and she is an alt. She is also an important part of our cleric team, so much so that she is one of the people that is keyed for Vex Thal (roughly half our guild is keyed at this point in time). So the opinion &quot;no alts before mains&quot; is just that - opinion, to be debated and not stated.<br>
<br>
The guilds &quot;overly represented&quot; on the list are undoubtedly those that heard about it when they went to Skyfire to complete a cleric's epic. These are the guilds that have helped support others who were camping Ragefire, who have continued to help, and who have made sure that Ragefire dies as fast as possible and without any despawns. If you're just learning about the list now, is it safe to assume that your guild had not sent anyone to Skyfire to camp Ragefire or to help someone else camp Ragefire recently? And yet now you wish to discuss being more entitled to a spawn than those on the list already? They're putting in work to earn that epic, for themselves and for others. What have you done so far?<br>
<br>
Getting on the list, as far as I know, is a matter of going to Skyfire and talking to the clerics there. I know there are some restrictions on things like certain guilds getting back-to-back spots on the list, but I hadn't heard that it was overly political. Do you have a specific example of someone being denied for political reasons? It would be a good idea to also post that to the Ragefire list board - I'm sure some of the other clerics on the list would be very interested to hear what happened.<br>
<br>
No consideration for other steps completed bothers me, as well. I wouldn't think of putting my name on the list unless I had all pieces ready to go to Timorous Deep. Again, something for the clerics on the list to decide - although seeing Mlain get the heart and not even have the note does irk me.<br>
<br>
List creation was done by people long gone from Skyfire. Who made the original listing (and it was four clerics long) is hardly relevant to today. Stacking of friends and guildmates is inevitable with any list - as people hear about it, they want in. And they'll hear about it sooner if they're guildmates or friends of people on the list, obviously. Controll in the hands of a few people - again, can you give some sort of example of what you mean by this? My understanding was that policy and procedures were decided by those on the list as a whole, not by a select few.<br>
<br>
And Desi. What would this debate be without you? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If every other spawn in the game is handled like that why not Ragefire. You sit your ass down there and you get in line behind the cleric who has been sitting there in front of you. You have to work / sleep ? Get someone to log your toon on and camp it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Waste guild time. Guarantee a gankfest, since CAMPING IS ALSO NOT SUPPORTED BY VERANT. Oh, and for good measure break the Terms of Service for EQ by giving account information to a second party. Yes, I can see how that would be a much more preferrable solution. /boggle<br>
<br>
Ragefire is unlike a standard camp in that the expected spawn time is on the order of days, not hours, and it is not a random probability of spawn. If you want Raster it doesn't matter when you camp him and when you sleep (modulo the game time theories on spawning him) - he's equally likely to pop for you during any of those sessions. If you want Ragefire, you have to stay for days in one sitting to get him. To have that requirement, and then to lump on top of it the chance that someone will come along and simply quote &quot;first to engage&quot; at you is cruel. The list attempts to bring civility to a camp where being civil has never really happened - and for four months, it has succeeded. That's why it's worth supporting. <br>
